title: Grateful Dead Live at Utica Memorial Auditorium on 1981-03-13
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other-> El Paso, Jack A Roe, Cassidy-> High Time, Little Red Rooster, Althea, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow-> Samson & Delilah, It Must Have Been The Roses, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Very nice, clear AUD Excellent show!

Live Taping Once again a Frank Streeter tape is beyond compare.
Love them all, but this one is the "SCHIZZLE."
43 years later and still fresh like the driven snow we walked out upon.

Great show Very nice recording of a wonderful night, excellent estimated/eyes and a prolonged jam inside Cassidy that was stellar. I have to say, Jerry and Bob’s interplay in this show was exceptional, and this recording really brings  that out.
Great show. Superb recording. I just had to comment to say this is one of the cleanest and best sounding audience recordings I've come across. Well done!
